Compare.graph_title: Trends in  Mesothelioma - Age Adjusted Rate - Total 2001-2005 to 2011-2015

info.info_how_calculated: Average annual number of residents diagnosed with mesothelioma over the 5 year period, divided by the corresponding age-specific intercensal population estimates (from NYS DOH). The resulting age-specific rates are multiplied by the proportion of the US Census 2000 standard population in each age group. Average age-adjusted rate is the sum of these weighted rates; expressed as cases per 100,000 residents.
